comment: Teague (IND) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Irving (CLE) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
James (CLE) makes marginal contact with George (IND) that does not affect his SQBR.
James (CLE) firms up his position and sets the screen on Teague (IND).
Irving (CLE) makes incidental contact with Teague (IND) that does not affect his ability to defend the play.
James (CLE) moves his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Turner (IND) legally contests James' (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Love (CLE) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with George (IND) that does not affect his SQBR.
James (CLE) cleanly strips the ball from Young (IND) and any contact after the deflection is considered incidental.
Stephenson (IND) commits a take foul on Korver (CLE).
George (IND) and James (CLE) briefly engage and separate off ball.
George (IND) sets the screen on Irving (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Irving (CLE) is in a legal guarding position while defending George (IND).
George (IND) moves his pivot foot prior to starting his dribble. The officials are looking for any illegal contact and do not pick up the pivot foot.
Turner (IND) commits a take foul on James (CLE).
